The paper deals with the computational complexity of case-based planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves analyzing and comparing different planning approaches, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of cases and libraries, which are common in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
